1
00:00:05,554 --> 00:00:06,972
Are you...

2
00:00:13,938 --> 00:00:16,232
It hurts...

3
00:00:17,441 --> 00:00:18,776
Screw this...!

4
00:00:24,740 --> 00:00:27,910
Is this some kind of trend or what?

5
00:00:41,131 --> 00:00:42,758
Levi, that's the guy!

6
00:00:42,758 --> 00:00:45,761
His level is the highest!

7
00:00:53,519 --> 00:00:54,562
Run!

8
00:00:59,316 --> 00:01:03,070
(Scum of the Brave)
No money to carry into tomorrow, so hungry, getting hit hard

9
00:01:03,070 --> 00:01:06,115
Playing bossa nova and
earning my day-to-day cash

10
00:01:06,866 --> 00:01:10,119
And the thugs
are running wild in the streets

11
00:01:10,119 --> 00:01:13,956
I'm just standing here,
staring at you with my dead-looking eyes

12
00:01:13,956 --> 00:01:18,752
There's not a single thing I can teach you

13
00:01:19,461 --> 00:01:20,921
Yeah...

14
00:01:20,921 --> 00:01:24,466
Let's just keep surviving over and over,
making fools of ourselves

15
00:01:24,466 --> 00:01:27,636
Since we're both not normal

16
00:01:29,263 --> 00:01:31,182
You can't save with "I-love-you"

17
00:01:31,182 --> 00:01:33,184
This town is sick

18
00:01:33,184 --> 00:01:36,687
Gradually, watching carefully,
get through it all

19
00:01:36,687 --> 00:01:40,191
That single moment in slow motion,
the battle's going good

20
00:01:40,191 --> 00:01:43,652
You and me,
we're so arrogant and so uncute

21
00:01:44,445 --> 00:01:46,113
Telling transparent lies

22
00:01:47,615 --> 00:01:51,493
Do you want to be strong?
Want to be loved?

23
00:01:51,493 --> 00:01:54,663
Stay quiet, you fool!

24
00:01:56,999 --> 00:01:59,001
Too early to say the "last of us"

25
00:01:59,001 --> 00:02:00,878
Today's day will soon be memorial

26
00:02:00,878 --> 00:02:04,048
Gradually, watching carefully,
bite into it and hang on

27
00:02:04,548 --> 00:02:06,967
Let's put on a poker face and go

28
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:09,678
Still the same, you and me,

29
00:02:09,678 --> 00:02:12,097
we're so arrogant and so uncute

30
00:02:12,097 --> 00:02:13,849
Telling transparent lies

31
00:02:13,849 --> 00:02:16,060
You can't save with "I-love-you"

32
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:23,526
You can't save a single soul

33
00:02:25,069 --> 00:02:27,029
Telling transparent lies

34
00:02:28,113 --> 00:02:32,785
(#7 The Death of a Brave)

35
00:02:33,202 --> 00:02:34,036
Hey!

36
00:02:34,787 --> 00:02:36,080
Let go of me!

37
00:02:41,293 --> 00:02:42,336
Dammit!

38
00:02:46,382 --> 00:02:48,884
It's not what you think it is.
I'm just...

39
00:02:51,303 --> 00:02:53,848
Don't waste my time.
Go.

40
00:02:57,309 --> 00:02:58,936
Get your ass movin'.
Now!

41
00:03:22,293 --> 00:03:24,253
She did track me after all.

42
00:03:25,504 --> 00:03:28,090
They might still be nearby.

43
00:03:28,799 --> 00:03:30,301
Let's track them.

44
00:03:31,177 --> 00:03:35,806
This chick has ether perception
that lets her hunt her mark.

45
00:03:47,902 --> 00:03:49,653
That badge...

46
00:03:50,404 --> 00:03:51,780
What's that mark?

47
00:03:53,866 --> 00:03:54,867
Dragon?

48
00:03:57,995 --> 00:03:59,830
She's actually dead set
on killing me.

49
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:04,376
Hey, let's not do this.

50
00:04:04,376 --> 00:04:07,880
It's gonna be a mess
if a guard pops up here, right?

51
00:04:08,172 --> 00:04:10,049
Fast reaction you got there.

52
00:04:10,049 --> 00:04:11,884
The enhancement type, huh?

53
00:04:12,885 --> 00:04:13,886
You can say...

54
00:04:19,433 --> 00:04:21,143
The tables have now turned.

55
00:04:21,769 --> 00:04:23,062
One thing, however.

56
00:04:24,271 --> 00:04:26,815
I won't negotiate.

57
00:04:28,776 --> 00:04:30,569
You've gotta be kidding me.

58
00:04:31,153 --> 00:04:33,572
This brat's losing
her damn mind.

59
00:04:46,460 --> 00:04:47,294
Master!

60
00:04:47,795 --> 00:04:50,297
Your beautiful disciple
has come to rescue you!

61
00:04:50,297 --> 00:04:53,551
Couldn't you put on a happier look?

62
00:04:55,636 --> 00:04:57,429
I told you to run.

63
00:04:57,429 --> 00:04:58,597
Where's Indo?

64
00:04:58,597 --> 00:04:59,765
She's fine!

65
00:04:59,765 --> 00:05:02,434
She's surely made
a clean escape by now.

66
00:05:02,434 --> 00:05:03,769
That's not what I meant.

67
00:05:03,769 --> 00:05:06,605
I'm telling you to bring
in a decent backup.

68
00:05:07,314 --> 00:05:08,816
Read the room, will ya!

69
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:13,737
And now,
I've got an extra block of dead weight,

70
00:05:13,737 --> 00:05:16,448
and that chick is physically
stronger than me.

71
00:05:17,032 --> 00:05:19,869
If I had a real sword,
I'd just chop off a few fingers.

72
00:05:20,369 --> 00:05:22,454
Too bad I only have this
toy with me.

73
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:28,586
Wish I could figure out what her
ether perception is sniffing...

74
00:05:31,422 --> 00:05:33,841
It's her sense of smell, Master.

75
00:05:36,093 --> 00:05:39,138
She seems to follow scent.

76
00:05:39,138 --> 00:05:40,014
Rather...

77
00:05:40,014 --> 00:05:43,350
She decisively identifies
how things would smell.

78
00:05:44,185 --> 00:05:47,062
For example,
like a well-polished mirror...

79
00:05:47,062 --> 00:05:52,359
No, like dripping watercolor
paint onto damp sand.

80
00:05:55,196 --> 00:05:56,739
Jogamine...

81
00:05:57,156 --> 00:05:58,574
Well done.

82
00:05:58,574 --> 00:06:00,242
Go jump off a bridge later.

83
00:06:00,242 --> 00:06:01,493
Y-Yes!

84
00:06:01,493 --> 00:06:03,287
I'm honored!

85
00:06:03,287 --> 00:06:06,207
It seems my literary talent
has proven useful!

86
00:06:06,207 --> 00:06:08,000
I wasn't praising you.

87
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,171
Besides, explain things
in under two secs next time.

88
00:06:12,171 --> 00:06:14,006
You yap too damn much!

89
00:06:17,593 --> 00:06:19,094
Allow me to treat you...

90
00:06:22,389 --> 00:06:25,059
...with an ultimate move.

91
00:06:25,059 --> 00:06:30,064
This is the bind state when
swords clash with one another.

92
00:06:30,564 --> 00:06:33,484
One wrong push or pull
and you're dead.

93
00:06:33,484 --> 00:06:35,402
A split-second clash.

94
00:06:35,402 --> 00:06:36,570
Which means,

95
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:38,572
the stage is now mine.

96
00:07:02,388 --> 00:07:04,515
G-Great work, Master!

97
00:07:05,015 --> 00:07:07,852
I've crushed her nose,
which is her key for tracking.

98
00:07:08,435 --> 00:07:10,938
But who the hell is she?

99
00:07:10,938 --> 00:07:13,899
At the very least,
she's not an official guard.

100
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,734
Should I kill her?

101
00:07:16,485 --> 00:07:18,904
Getting rid of her corpse
would be a hassle, though...

102
00:07:18,904 --> 00:07:19,947
Master!

103
00:07:21,365 --> 00:07:24,410
I'd stop if I were you.

104
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:28,163
If we fight here,
one of us is going to die.

105
00:07:29,164 --> 00:07:31,041
You're strong, huh?

106
00:07:32,293 --> 00:07:33,544
I get that a lot.

107
00:07:33,544 --> 00:07:35,629
What's the deal with her?

108
00:07:35,629 --> 00:07:39,425
She ain't no assassin sent
after me, right? She a mad dog or what?

109
00:07:39,425 --> 00:07:41,010
Sorry about her.

110
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:44,430
Guess she got a little worked up
after you guys got the upper hand.

111
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:46,182
She's got a lot of pride.

112
00:07:46,182 --> 00:07:48,267
Aight.
You wanna have at it, too?

113
00:07:48,267 --> 00:07:49,310
Nah.

114
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:52,021
How about we both
just call it a day?

115
00:07:53,314 --> 00:07:56,609
I'll turn a blind eye to this.

116
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:04,200
If you actually reflected on this,
then we'll spare you.

117
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:07,369
But never trespass
on our Academy again!

118
00:08:07,369 --> 00:08:11,123
My master and I will stop you
as many times as it takes!

119
00:08:11,123 --> 00:08:12,541
Well, much obliged.

120
00:08:12,541 --> 00:08:14,210
What say you, Mister Master?

121
00:08:16,837 --> 00:08:18,255
We're leaving.

122
00:08:18,255 --> 00:08:19,215
Yes!

123
00:08:19,215 --> 00:08:21,217
Bye.

124
00:08:31,268 --> 00:08:32,645
My Master...

125
00:08:33,729 --> 00:08:37,608
He called that move
the "drawing in" technique.

126
00:08:39,109 --> 00:08:41,862
Once you lock swords in a bind,
you give it a little push.

127
00:08:42,363 --> 00:08:45,115
If the opponent
reflexively pushes back,

128
00:08:45,616 --> 00:08:48,369
you pull your sword and
break their balance.

129
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,122
If they, instead,
try to pull away,

130
00:08:52,122 --> 00:08:53,916
the bind comes loose,

131
00:08:53,916 --> 00:08:54,833
Yashiro Punch!

132
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,585
and that's when you strike.

133
00:08:58,254 --> 00:09:00,923
Easier said than done, though.

134
00:09:01,507 --> 00:09:03,008
It takes practice and experience.

135
00:09:03,425 --> 00:09:04,510
Master.

136
00:09:04,510 --> 00:09:09,473
Was that a special lecture
to reward my devotion?

137
00:09:09,974 --> 00:09:12,017
Don't make me laugh.

138
00:09:12,017 --> 00:09:17,857
What were you on to end up with
such a dumb, happy-go-lucky brain?

139
00:09:17,857 --> 00:09:19,608
Too much E3?

140
00:09:19,608 --> 00:09:21,318
No, that's not it.

141
00:09:22,361 --> 00:09:23,863
I'm the same as you, Master.

142
00:09:24,655 --> 00:09:28,909
My father often told me
stories about you.

143
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:30,411
Huh?

144
00:09:31,287 --> 00:09:36,375
I can't describe how moved I was
when we first met that night.

145
00:09:37,668 --> 00:09:39,795
Hurry and get yourself
to the hospital.

146
00:09:40,045 --> 00:09:41,046
See ya.

147
00:09:41,797 --> 00:09:44,300
You don't look as gentle,
so I was shocked at first.

148
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:47,303
A delinquent-looking loser,
saying the kindest things.

149
00:09:47,303 --> 00:09:48,596
That was my impression.

150
00:09:49,430 --> 00:09:52,308
But it all makes sense once
I delved into your thoughts.

151
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:53,934
Wait.

152
00:09:55,394 --> 00:09:58,439
What's the name of your father?

153
00:09:58,939 --> 00:10:01,942
Kiyohito Takamiya.

154
00:10:03,444 --> 00:10:07,323
And you'd be right in saying
that he is your master, Master.

155
00:10:16,081 --> 00:10:18,792
Are you... not aware of this?

156
00:10:18,792 --> 00:10:21,462
I thought Mr. Ishinoo had told you.

157
00:10:23,839 --> 00:10:26,091
When my parents divorced,

158
00:10:26,091 --> 00:10:28,469
I went with my mother,

159
00:10:29,011 --> 00:10:31,847
but I was still able to see
my father once a month.

160
00:10:33,724 --> 00:10:38,479
Each time, he told me about how
wonderful the job of a Brave was.

161
00:10:38,479 --> 00:10:40,731
That master of mine?

162
00:10:40,731 --> 00:10:42,983
Talking about how wonderful the job was?

163
00:10:43,609 --> 00:10:46,612
I respect my father, Master.

164
00:10:47,154 --> 00:10:50,282
Why did you decide to become a Brave?

165
00:10:58,374 --> 00:10:59,750
It was seven years ago.

166
00:11:07,341 --> 00:11:10,970
I dropped out of high school
for personal reasons

167
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:12,930
and got kicked out of
my family's house.

168
00:11:13,514 --> 00:11:18,394
I ended up part-timing under some
small-time Demon King around Ikebukuro.

169
00:11:24,024 --> 00:11:26,402
Back then, the west side
of the Yamanote Line...

170
00:11:26,402 --> 00:11:29,822
...was a battleground crowded
with upstart Demon Kings,

171
00:11:29,822 --> 00:11:33,033
which made it a perfect
hunting ground for Braves.

172
00:11:37,204 --> 00:11:39,999
The one who came strolling in...

173
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:42,293
...and stole my job...

174
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,588
...was "Nine-Finger" Kiyohito Takamiya.

175
00:11:58,893 --> 00:12:01,604
After my employer was killed,

176
00:12:02,188 --> 00:12:03,397
I was in a bind.

177
00:12:04,523 --> 00:12:11,238
So I had no choice but to become his
apprentice and serve as his assistant.

178
00:12:17,453 --> 00:12:21,957
I believe my father understood
the feelings of the weak.

179
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:25,753
That's why he held such high ideals.

180
00:12:26,545 --> 00:12:29,048
Even in the line of work that
could be sinful at times,

181
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:31,467
he still had the will
to pursue what was best.

182
00:12:33,469 --> 00:12:39,058
He always told me happily about
your exploits as his disciple.

183
00:12:39,058 --> 00:12:41,101
He said you had extraordinary talent,

184
00:12:41,101 --> 00:12:43,229
a Brave with a bright future.

185
00:12:43,938 --> 00:12:48,275
Your battle with Lord "Radiance Serpent"
and the Shinjuku 6/17 conflict.

186
00:12:52,029 --> 00:12:54,281
What the hell is this discrepancy?

187
00:12:55,032 --> 00:12:57,368
That's nothing like the master I knew.

188
00:12:58,619 --> 00:13:01,288
The master I knew was cowardly,
bad at handling pressure.

189
00:13:01,789 --> 00:13:04,250
A man who always seemed
to be afraid of something.

190
00:13:05,501 --> 00:13:10,381
And that's exactly why he was
meticulous, ruthless, and merciless.

191
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:14,760
"Bein' a Brave is a gig
for the scummiest scum."

192
00:13:16,095 --> 00:13:18,138
He used to say that all the time.

193
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:21,725
"It's not a job you stick with for long.

194
00:13:22,393 --> 00:13:25,312
Once you've made a decent pile of cash,
you should head off to Hawaii,

195
00:13:25,312 --> 00:13:28,065
catch some fish,
and live out your days."

196
00:13:29,483 --> 00:13:33,237
I also think this line of work is shitty.

197
00:13:34,822 --> 00:13:36,448
It's been years...

198
00:13:37,339 --> 00:13:38,758
...since his passing.

199
00:13:50,004 --> 00:13:53,799
Looks like he was lying to you.

200
00:13:54,842 --> 00:13:59,930
An ideal Brave is someone who
likes killing and is good at it.

201
00:14:01,932 --> 00:14:02,933
Still...

202
00:14:02,933 --> 00:14:06,270
It remains true that you saved us.

203
00:14:06,270 --> 00:14:10,941
Aren't those words different
from your own ideals?

204
00:14:15,654 --> 00:14:16,864
Is it?

205
00:14:17,323 --> 00:14:19,700
That's what your old man taught me.

206
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,860
No, Master.
It's you...

207
00:14:31,712 --> 00:14:32,713
Go home.

208
00:14:45,851 --> 00:14:47,520
My head hurts...

209
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,104
Is the E3 causing this?

210
00:14:49,730 --> 00:14:50,731
No...

211
00:14:51,398 --> 00:14:53,526
It's Jogamine's fault.

212
00:14:54,193 --> 00:14:56,612
I should get back to Ed's bar.

213
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,114
Get some beers,

214
00:15:00,783 --> 00:15:01,784
eat some pizza,

215
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:04,745
play some card games.

216
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:13,045
My own version of a good world.

217
00:15:16,090 --> 00:15:21,095
(Scum of the Brave)

218
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:27,226
You're late.

219
00:15:27,226 --> 00:15:28,102
Huh?

220
00:15:30,855 --> 00:15:32,857
What were you doing?

221
00:15:32,857 --> 00:15:34,358
Eating a hamburger.

222
00:15:34,358 --> 00:15:35,776
Liar.

223
00:15:35,776 --> 00:15:37,236
I'm serious.

224
00:15:37,778 --> 00:15:38,988
Ed...

225
00:15:38,988 --> 00:15:40,239
No, where's the manager?

226
00:15:40,239 --> 00:15:44,326
He left so suddenly, saying that
he's going out to eat.

227
00:15:44,326 --> 00:15:46,704
He left with this guy named Maruta.

228
00:15:46,704 --> 00:15:49,623
How does this place
even stay in business?

229
00:15:50,291 --> 00:15:52,877
You should've just gone home.

230
00:15:52,877 --> 00:15:55,379
It's already late.

231
00:15:55,671 --> 00:15:57,047
What are you, a delinquent?

232
00:15:58,757 --> 00:16:01,635
How can I not be worried after
the way we parted like that?

233
00:16:02,094 --> 00:16:04,013
I'm worried about whether
you were okay or not.

234
00:16:06,223 --> 00:16:08,934
You're surprisingly reasonable.

235
00:16:08,934 --> 00:16:11,020
Huh?! Are you making fun of me?!

236
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:13,022
No, I'm complimenting you.

237
00:16:13,606 --> 00:16:16,525
As in, you've got common sense.

238
00:16:16,525 --> 00:16:19,403
You're a considerate,
decent person.

239
00:16:23,032 --> 00:16:24,200
Shut up!

240
00:16:27,161 --> 00:16:28,913
Your ether perception...

241
00:16:29,413 --> 00:16:31,040
...it tells you where enemies are.

242
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:34,210
Or rather, it tells you their strength.

243
00:16:35,878 --> 00:16:38,214
Not in images or numbers,

244
00:16:38,839 --> 00:16:41,926
rather a sixth sense type?

245
00:16:43,052 --> 00:16:44,345
Yeah.

246
00:16:44,970 --> 00:16:50,059
My dad said it lets me feel an opponent's
strength and the level of threat.

247
00:16:50,809 --> 00:16:54,188
Like heat or pressure...

248
00:16:54,188 --> 00:16:56,065
...that kind of dangerous feeling.

249
00:16:56,857 --> 00:16:59,818
Well, you were fine against
that monster the other day,

250
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:02,947
but nearly collapsed in front
of that tiny woman.

251
00:17:02,947 --> 00:17:05,032
There's no other explanation.

252
00:17:07,910 --> 00:17:10,829
Yeah... I was scared.

253
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:13,457
You probably think I'm not
cut out to be a Brave, right?

254
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:15,042
Yeah.

255
00:17:16,669 --> 00:17:20,339
You're a good person,
so quit being a Brave.

256
00:17:21,423 --> 00:17:23,843
Like hell I will, you idiot.

257
00:17:32,434 --> 00:17:37,022
My master told me that being afraid of
your enemies is nothing to be ashamed of.

258
00:17:37,898 --> 00:17:41,902
But you have to control it,
lest you die.

259
00:17:43,612 --> 00:17:45,906
Only lots of experience will
get you used to it.

260
00:17:47,449 --> 00:17:51,078
No one talks for Jogamine, though.
She's a special kind of nut.

261
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:54,915
That brat...

262
00:17:57,751 --> 00:17:59,962
You know...

263
00:18:00,796 --> 00:18:04,341
What's the deal with her?!
When she's not even reading minds, but...

264
00:18:04,341 --> 00:18:06,135
How do you even deal with her?

265
00:18:06,677 --> 00:18:07,553
Ah...

266
00:18:07,553 --> 00:18:12,558
It's not like she is trying
to read our minds.

267
00:18:13,475 --> 00:18:16,562
She'd tell us
if she's using her ability.

268
00:18:16,562 --> 00:18:19,398
Apparently with people
she's just met,

269
00:18:19,398 --> 00:18:22,902
it's hard for her to block their channel,
so she ends up hearing things.

270
00:18:23,569 --> 00:18:28,032
I don't think she'll read you
unless she has to.

271
00:18:29,575 --> 00:18:31,410
Did something happen?

272
00:18:31,410 --> 00:18:32,536
Nothing.

273
00:18:33,704 --> 00:18:36,373
I've only been teamed up
with her since the last training,

274
00:18:36,373 --> 00:18:38,250
so I don't know her well.

275
00:18:39,501 --> 00:18:41,212
But she's not a bad person.

276
00:18:41,212 --> 00:18:43,339
"Not a bad person"?

277
00:18:43,339 --> 00:18:46,592
That's what people would say
when they've got nothing good to say.

278
00:18:46,592 --> 00:18:49,845
Well, I do think that she's weird.

279
00:18:49,845 --> 00:18:52,640
She meddles when nobody asks,

280
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:56,852
and shows up to help even
when she's obviously useless.

281
00:18:56,852 --> 00:19:01,607
It's like she runs on sheer
stubbornness or something.

282
00:19:01,607 --> 00:19:04,652
But I don't really dislike her.

283
00:19:04,652 --> 00:19:07,238
That Jogamine, I mean.

284
00:19:07,238 --> 00:19:09,448
I do hate her!

285
00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:11,617
I'm telling you this because
you're a good person!

286
00:19:12,493 --> 00:19:13,661
That kind of person...

287
00:19:20,084 --> 00:19:21,752
'Sup, Joe.

288
00:19:21,752 --> 00:19:23,754
Ed Cyrus isn't present
at the moment.

289
00:19:23,754 --> 00:19:26,131
Got back from work?

290
00:19:26,131 --> 00:19:28,008
Did you already screw up?

291
00:19:28,008 --> 00:19:29,051
Shut the hell up.

292
00:19:29,051 --> 00:19:30,261
Oh, right.

293
00:19:30,261 --> 00:19:33,264
Maruta finally paid
a visit here after a while.

294
00:19:33,764 --> 00:19:36,058
Looks like he went out with Ed,

295
00:19:36,058 --> 00:19:38,644
but while they're gone,
let's go grab some food too.

296
00:19:40,396 --> 00:19:41,355
Joe?

297
00:19:44,024 --> 00:19:45,359
Ah, nothing...

298
00:19:45,359 --> 00:19:47,653
Yashiro, what are you gonna do?

299
00:19:47,653 --> 00:19:50,406
What do you mean,
what am I gonna do?

300
00:19:50,990 --> 00:19:53,534
I saw it on the evening news.

301
00:19:54,493 --> 00:19:57,705
I then asked someone
who knows the details.

302
00:19:59,206 --> 00:20:02,668
They found a corpse
with a goofy face...

303
00:20:02,668 --> 00:20:05,713
...in an alley in Shin-Okubo
this morning.

304
00:20:12,553 --> 00:20:13,804
Then it must be...

305
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:16,515
It's honestly ridiculous.

306
00:20:16,515 --> 00:20:18,392
I saw the photos.

307
00:20:18,934 --> 00:20:23,939
He's stabbed all over, with a
finishing blow to the throat.

308
00:20:24,231 --> 00:20:27,276
His neck was split open like this.

309
00:20:27,276 --> 00:20:30,946
Even if he came back as a ghost,
he wouldn't be able to talk.

310
00:20:32,198 --> 00:20:33,824
I see.

311
00:20:33,824 --> 00:20:35,201
He's already...

312
00:20:35,201 --> 00:20:37,703
Also, look at this.

313
00:20:40,956 --> 00:20:43,417
Apparently the body was clutching it.

314
00:20:53,928 --> 00:20:57,473
Pretty nice, right? So when are we
having the funeral party?

315
00:20:59,308 --> 00:21:00,392
Yeah.

316
00:21:00,392 --> 00:21:02,770
After we've done taking care of
the thing that we should've first.

317
00:21:21,205 --> 00:21:23,707
What? What happened?

318
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:27,294
You guys look scary.

319
00:21:31,298 --> 00:21:32,883
Pretty sure you're just seeing things.

320
00:22:36,008 --> 00:22:38,594
We'll find the one who killed Ishinoo,

321
00:22:38,957 --> 00:22:41,418
and make them suffer worse than hell.

322
00:22:42,237 --> 00:22:46,866
That's the only thing
bastards like us can do.

323
00:22:46,891 --> 00:22:50,007
(#8 The Sin of the Brave)
